The Vice President, Joe Biden, expressed his condolences for the passing of Dr. Benjamin Hooks, a civil rights hero. Dr. Hooks served as the head of the NAACP from 1977 to 1992 and was known for his commitment to eliminating racism and creating a more just America. He used his position as an ordained minister to inspire others to believe in the importance of civil rights, not just for black men and women, but for the entire country. The Vice President praised Dr. Hooks' actions, stating that he helped write a better history, and encouraged others to follow his lead in building a better future.